node.text: As the Olympic spirit sweeps the nation, let former Olympic gymnast Emilie Goldblum guide you through a restorative #WorkoutWednesday. From competing in the 2000 Summer Games in Sydney to performing with #Cher and #TheWeeknd, Emilie has done it all, so she’s no stranger to looking after her body to avoid injuries. Join in as she takes you through a 20 minute stretch session, and tag @BritishVogue in your next #WorkoutWednesday video to let us know where you're taking part.

node.text: The founder of @AnniesIbiza – one of #KateMoss’s go-to stores for rare, one-of-a-kind vintage – Annie Doble takes #BritishVogue through five of her current wardrobe favourites. From a summer-ready silk slip dress to a party dress embellished with feathers and sustainable sequins, and a rare vintage Thierry Mugler rainbow jacket, watch as Annie walks us through her most-loved looks from her Ibiza home.

node.text: It’s a well-known fact that wearing SPF is one of the best ways to protect your skin – but how do you do it right to avoid signs of ageing and pigmentation? Watch as #BritishVogue’s beauty and lifestyle director @JessicaDiner does a sunscreen deep dive with @LaRochePosay dermatologist Dr Hiva Fassihi to discuss how to incorporate SPF into your everyday make-up routine (and why make-up with SPF isn’t enough), the difference between the effects of ultraviolet A and ultraviolet B on your skin, and why it’s important to apply sunscreen even if you’re not leaving the house.

node.title: Face Facts: The Importance Of SPF No Matter The Season

node.text:
Starring Academy Award-winner #JenniferHudson, ‘Respect’ charts the rise of the Queen of Soul, #ArethaFranklin. Hudson, who was personally chosen by Franklin for the film, portrays how that irrepressible and unmistakable voice came to embody the resilience of the African-American community during the civil rights, Black Power and feminist movements. Ahead of the biopic’s release, Tony Award-winning costume designer @ClintRamos discusses how he authentically brought the icon’s style to life on screen, at the link in bio.

Photographed by @PhotoDre.

node.text: The volatility of the British weather during the summer months has made us adept at rain-proofing our wardrobes. The perfect storm attire is made up of puddle-proof platform soles or stomper boots; luxe waterproofs in the shape of colour-pop macs or vinyl trench coats; and slouchy clutch bags big enough to stash an umbrella – or better yet, a bucket hat. Click the link in bio for the AW21 street-style approved looks in which to navigate a storm in style.

node.text:
As September rolls forward, it’s time to introduce the shape of autumn to your wardrobes. Historically signifying a gear shift for Vogue, this year’s September issue holds particular gravitas. In the spirit of collaboration, four fashion editors from across the globe join forces to showcase some of the biggest trends. It’s a joy-inducing assortment of ideas and inspiration. See the full story in the new issue and at the link in bio now.

@JumboJanet_, @EdieBCampbell, @Ka.ya.ko and @AdutAkech photographed by @Studio_Jackson and styled by @Alex_Jordan_Harrington, @PoppyKain, Camilla Nickerson and @SarrJamois. With hair by @CyndiaHarvey and @JimmyPaulHair, colouring by @MadsSune, braiding by @ColeUnique1 and @WayneShorterCampbell, make-up by @DickPageFace and @Hiromi_Ueda, with nails by @AdamSlee_ and @YukoTsuchihashi and production by @HonorHellonProd.

node.text:
In her sixties, gallerist and artist @Julia.PeytonJones decided to devote her life to something new: motherhood. In the September 2021 issue of #BritishVogue, she reflects on her journey towards becoming a mother, and how her daughter Pia lit up her life, and her art. “I learnt every day about motherhood, with much hilarity as well as tears. I wanted to keep us both under wraps and only peek out from under the blankets to see what was happening in the world. But I knew from the moment I saw her that she was a gift from God, a treasured creature whom I would do everything in my power to nurture and protect. I knew that I would draw on every conceivable resource that I possibly could to become the mother she deserves me to be,” she writes. Ahead of the release of her new book #PiasWorld, see the full story in the new issue and read her essay at the link in bio now.

#JuliaPeytonJones photographed by @_AdamaJalloh and styled by @EnieD, with hair by @AndreaMarin0 and make-up by @EmmaSmallHairAndMakeup.

node.text:
Preparing for her next chapter, #ShadowAndBone star @Jessie_Mei_Li is ready to take the world by storm in her upcoming role in Edgar Wright’s film #LastNightInSoho alongside #AnyaTaylorJoy. “I’m not one to plan ahead, but hopefully I’ll find myself in some interesting places,” she says. “I like not knowing what’s coming my way,” she tells #BritishVogue in the September 2021 issue. See the full story in the new issue and at the link in bio now.
 
#JessieMeiLi wears all @Prada, photographed by @RafaelPavarotti_ and styled by @Edward_Enninful, with hair by @EugeneSouleiman, make-up by @AmmyDrammeh, nails by @AmaQuashie, set design by @IbbyNjoya, flowers by @S2EventsLtd and production by @LalalandProductions.
